Today, I started my web development journey by learning the fundamentals of HTML and CSS. I practiced creating a basic webpage, adding links, designing buttons, and applying simple CSS styles and hover effects.
ðŸŸ¦ HTML Basics
âœ… What I Learned

HTML is the structure of a webpage. Tags are used to define elements like headings, paragraphs, and links.

ðŸ”¹ Basic HTML Structure I wrote:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>My First HTML Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My HTML Learning</h1>
    <p>This is my first paragraph in HTML.</p>
</body>
</html>

ðŸŸ¦ Anchor Tag (<a>)
âœ… What I Learned

The anchor tag helps create clickable links.

ðŸ”¹ Normal Link:
<a href="https://google.com">Go to Google</a>

ðŸ”¹ Open Link in New Tab:
<a href="https://google.com" target="_blank">Open Google in New Tab</a>

ðŸ”¹ Anchor Tag as a Button:
<a href="#" class="btn">Read More</a>

ðŸŸ© CSS Basics
âœ… What I Learned

CSS is used to style a webpage. There are three ways to use CSS.

ðŸ”¹ Inline CSS:
<p style="color: green;">This is green text.</p>

ðŸ”¹ Internal CSS:
<style>
    p {
        font-size: 18px;
        color: blue;
    }
</style>

ðŸ”¹ External CSS:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

ðŸŸ¦ Buttons in HTML & CSS
ðŸ”¹ Basic HTML Button:
<button>Click Me</button>

ðŸ”¹ Styled Button with CSS:
<style>
button {
    background-color: #4CAF50;
    padding: 10px 20px;
    color: white;
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}
</style>

ðŸŸ¦ Hover Effects
ðŸ”¹ Hover on Link:
a:hover {
    color: red;
}

ðŸ”¹ Hover on Button:
button:hover {
    background-color: darkgreen;
}

ðŸ”¹ Hover on Styled Anchor Button:
.btn:hover {
    background-color: #006f94;
}

ðŸŸ¦ Final Combined Example (All-in-One)

Here is one simple page combining everything I learned today:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Today's Learning</title>

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        a {
            color: blue;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        a:hover {
            color: red;
        }

        .btn {
            background-color: #008CBA;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #006f94;
        }

        button {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        button:hover {
            background-color: darkgreen;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <h1>Today I Learned â€” HTML & CSS Basics</h1>

    <p>This page contains everything I learned today including HTML basics, anchor tags, CSS, buttons, and hover effects.</p>

    <h2>Anchor Tag Example</h2>
    <a href="https://google.com" target="_blank">Open Google</a>

    <h2>Button Example</h2>
    <button>Click Me</button>

    <h2>Styled Anchor Button</h2>
    <a href="#" class="btn">Read More</a>

</body>
</html>

